@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "User (Analyst)" as User
actor "External Data Source" as ExternalAPI

rectangle "DataInsight AI System" {

  usecase "Upload Multimodal Data" as UC1
  usecase "Ingest External Data" as UC2
  usecase "Process Data by Modality" as UC3
  usecase "Run AI Analysis Task" as UC4
  usecase "Search & Query Insights" as UC5
  usecase "View Explainable Results" as UC6
}

User --> UC1
User --> UC5
User --> UC6

ExternalAPI --> UC2

UC1 --> UC3
UC2 --> UC3
UC3 --> UC4
UC4 --> UC6

@enduml

note right of User
The User (Analyst) is the primary actor who interacts with the system to upload data, initiate analysis tasks, query insights, and review explainable results for decision-making.
end note

note right of ExternalAPI
The External Data Source represents third-party systems such as document repositories, news APIs, or video platforms that provide data for ingestion into the system.
end note

note right of UC1
This use case allows the user to upload documents, images, audio, or video files into the system through a unified interface.
end note

note right of UC2
This use case enables the system to ingest data programmatically from external APIs or repositories.
end note

note right of UC3
This use case processes incoming data based on its modality using specialized pipelines such as OCR, speech recognition, or video analysis.
end note

note right of UC4
This use case applies AI tasks such as summarization, classification, or question answering to processed data.
end note

note right of UC5
This use case allows users to query the extracted knowledge using natural language search.
end note

note right of UC6
This use case presents results along with traceable evidence to ensure transparency and trust.
end note
